Package: UK2GTFS
Type: Package
Title: Convert UK Transport Timetable Datasets to GTFS Format
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Malcolm", "Morgan", email = "m.morgan1@leeds.ac.uk", role = c("aut","cre","cph"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9488-9183")),
    person("Adrian", "Schönig", role = c("ctb")),
    person("Owen", "O'Neill", email = "owen@wvr.org.uk", role = c("aut"), 
      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0008-0595-3042"))
    )
Maintainer: Malcolm Morgan <m.morgan1@leeds.ac.uk>
Description: Convert transport timetable data from the formats used in
    the United Kingdom to the General Transit Feed Specification ('GTFS')
    format. Supports the Common Interface File ('CIF') format used by the
    Rail Delivery Group and Network Rail for heavy and light rail
    timetables, 'TransXChange' XML files used for bus, coach, and ferry
    timetables, and the historic National Public Transport Data
    Repository ('NPTDR') archives. Also provides utilities for reading,
    writing, cleaning, subsetting, and merging 'GTFS' files.
